begemotSnmpd.name: begemotSnmpd
begemotSnmpd.contactinfo: Hartmut Brandt Postal: Fraunhofer Institute for Open Communication Systems Kaiserin-Augusta-Allee 31 10589 Berlin Germany Fax: +49 30 3463 7352 E-mail: harti@freebsd.org
begemotSnmpd.description: The MIB module for the Begemot SNMP daemon.

SectionName.name: SectionName
SectionName.description: Name of a loadable module. Should consist of alphanumeric characers only, the first character must be a letter.

begemotSnmpdAgentFreeBSD.name: begemotSnmpdAgentFreeBSD
begemotSnmpdAgentFreeBSD.description: Identifies the agent as running on FreeBSD.

begemotSnmpdTransmitBuffer.name: begemotSnmpdTransmitBuffer
begemotSnmpdTransmitBuffer.description: The size of the receive buffer in bytes. Larger messages are dropped by SNMPd.

begemotSnmpdReceiveBuffer.name: begemotSnmpdReceiveBuffer
begemotSnmpdReceiveBuffer.description: The size of the transmit buffer in bytes. Larger messages cannot be sent by the SNMPd.

begemotSnmpdCommunityDisable.name: begemotSnmpdCommunityDisable
begemotSnmpdCommunityDisable.description: Disables all access to the CommunityTable from SNMP. Once set it cannot be cleared.

begemotSnmpdTrap1Addr.name: begemotSnmpdTrap1Addr
begemotSnmpdTrap1Addr.description: The trap sink for v1 traps.

begemotSnmpdVersionEnable.name: begemotSnmpdVersionEnable
begemotSnmpdVersionEnable.description: The SNMP versions that the agent processes. The following bits are defined: 0x00000001 - SNMPv1 0x00000002 - SNMPv2c

begemotTrapSinkTable.name: begemotTrapSinkTable
begemotTrapSinkTable.description: A table with destinations for standard traps.

begemotTrapSinkAddr.name: begemotTrapSinkAddr
begemotTrapSinkAddr.description: Destination IP address of the manager station where to send traps.

begemotTrapSinkPort.name: begemotTrapSinkPort
begemotTrapSinkPort.description: Destination UDP port of the manager station where to send traps.

begemotSnmpdPortTable.name: begemotSnmpdPortTable
begemotSnmpdPortTable.description: A table with descriptions of UDP ports to listen on for SNMP messages.

begemotSnmpdPortEntry.name: begemotSnmpdPortEntry
begemotSnmpdPortEntry.description: An entry in the table with descriptions of UDP ports to listen on for SNMP messages.

begemotSnmpdPortAddress.name: begemotSnmpdPortAddress
begemotSnmpdPortAddress.description: The IP address to bind to.

begemotSnmpdPortPort.name: begemotSnmpdPortPort
begemotSnmpdPortPort.description: The UDP port to listen on for SNMP messages.

begemotSnmpdPortStatus.name: begemotSnmpdPortStatus
begemotSnmpdPortStatus.description: Set status to 1 to create entry, set it to 2 to delete it.

begemotSnmpdCommunityTable.name: begemotSnmpdCommunityTable
begemotSnmpdCommunityTable.description: A table with the community strings for access control.

begemotSnmpdCommunityEntry.name: begemotSnmpdCommunityEntry
begemotSnmpdCommunityEntry.description: A table with the community strings for access control. When begemotSnmpdCommDisable is true, this table disappears.

begemotSnmpdCommunityModule.name: begemotSnmpdCommunityModule
begemotSnmpdCommunityModule.description: Index of the module that has registered this community. For global communities this is the empty string.

begemotSnmpdCommunityIndex.name: begemotSnmpdCommunityIndex
begemotSnmpdCommunityIndex.description: The numerical index of the community (private to the module).

begemotSnmpdCommunityString.name: begemotSnmpdCommunityString
begemotSnmpdCommunityString.description: The string for access to SNMPd.

begemotSnmpdCommunityDescr.name: begemotSnmpdCommunityDescr
begemotSnmpdCommunityDescr.description: A description what this community is good for.

begemotSnmpdModuleTable.name: begemotSnmpdModuleTable
begemotSnmpdModuleTable.description: A table describing all the currently loaded dynamic modules. Writing to this table loads and unloads modules.

begemotSnmpdModuleEntry.name: begemotSnmpdModuleEntry
begemotSnmpdModuleEntry.description: A table entry describing a loadable module.

begemotSnmpdModuleSection.name: begemotSnmpdModuleSection
begemotSnmpdModuleSection.description: The string used for matching configuration file sections and indexes the module table.

begemotSnmpdModulePath.name: begemotSnmpdModulePath
begemotSnmpdModulePath.description: The path name of the module. Set to empty string to unload a module. The path of an existing module may not be changed.

begemotSnmpdStatsNoRxBufs.name: begemotSnmpdStatsNoRxBufs
begemotSnmpdStatsNoRxBufs.description: Number of times a receive buffer could not be allocated for a packet.

begemotSnmpdStatsNoTxBufs.name: begemotSnmpdStatsNoTxBufs
begemotSnmpdStatsNoTxBufs.description: Number of times a transmit buffer could not be allocated for a packet.

begemotSnmpdStatsInTooLongPkts.name: begemotSnmpdStatsInTooLongPkts
begemotSnmpdStatsInTooLongPkts.description: Number of packets received that were longer than the receive buffer. These packets are dropped.

begemotSnmpdStatsInBadPduTypes.name: begemotSnmpdStatsInBadPduTypes
begemotSnmpdStatsInBadPduTypes.description: Number of packets received with a bad type field.

begemotSnmpdDebugDumpPdus.name: begemotSnmpdDebugDumpPdus
begemotSnmpdDebugDumpPdus.description: Dump PDUs to log file if true.

begemotSnmpdDebugSnmpTrace.name: begemotSnmpdDebugSnmpTrace
begemotSnmpdDebugSnmpTrace.description: Tracing flags for the SNMP library. These flags have the following meaning: 0x00000001 trace GET operator 0x00000002 trace GETNEXT operator 0x00000004 trace SET operator 0x00000008 trace dependency processing 0x00000010 trace node finding 0x10000000 log ASN1 errors 0x20000000 log SNMP errors Individual values can be or-ed together.

begemotSnmpdDebugSyslogPri.name: begemotSnmpdDebugSyslogPri
begemotSnmpdDebugSyslogPri.description: Events with this or higher priority should not be logged.

begemotSnmpdLocalPortTable.name: begemotSnmpdLocalPortTable
begemotSnmpdLocalPortTable.description: A table with descriptions of local (unix domain) ports to listen on for SNMP messages.

begemotSnmpdLocalPortEntry.name: begemotSnmpdLocalPortEntry
begemotSnmpdLocalPortEntry.description: An entry in the table with descriptions of local ports to listen on for SNMP messages.

begemotSnmpdLocalPortPath.name: begemotSnmpdLocalPortPath
begemotSnmpdLocalPortPath.description: The path name to create and listen on.

begemotSnmpdLocalPortStatus.name: begemotSnmpdLocalPortStatus
begemotSnmpdLocalPortStatus.description: Set status to 1 to create entry, set it to 2 to delete it.

begemotSnmpdLocalPortType.name: begemotSnmpdLocalPortType
begemotSnmpdLocalPortType.description: Type of the port. If the type is unpriv SET operations are allowed from all clients if the community matches. For priv SET operations are allowed only from peers with uid zero. If the daemon cannot determine the peer uid it disallows the SET operation for -priv ports.

begemotSnmpdTransportTable.name: begemotSnmpdTransportTable
begemotSnmpdTransportTable.description: A table containing all the currently loaded transport mappings.

begemotSnmpdTransportEntry.name: begemotSnmpdTransportEntry
begemotSnmpdTransportEntry.description: An entry in the table with the transport mappings.

begemotSnmpdTransportOid.name: begemotSnmpdTransportOid
begemotSnmpdTransportOid.description: A pointer to the group with the transport-dependend stuff.
